cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a differentiable interpreter for a programming language that can be optimized through gradient descent techniques. It also discusses the incorporation of prior knowledge into a model, which is a common topic in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of a neural implementation of a programming language and the use of prior procedural knowledge to solve tasks. 

The paper also touches on cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it presents a differentiable interpreter for the programming language Forth. 

It could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses the optimization of program behaviour through gradient descent techniques and the integration of the program into a larger neural computation graph. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it presents a neural implementation of the dual stack machine that underlies Forth and discusses the optimization of program behaviour through gradient descent techniques.
